text:
Ann is a great host. She is soft spoken and a very generous person. When I was tired from a long journey, she prepared a delicious borscht soup for me. It meant a lot to me, as it was not just food but also Russian hospitality at it's best filled with warmth and love. I felt like a family after traveling for so many days alone. Also she is very fluent in English as she is an English teacher at a school in Novosibirsk.

Watch out for her son Sasha. He is full of fun and a very intelligent young boy. I had a good time hanging out with him. 

Yes, I would definitely recommend her to other couchsurfers.

Very nice and true hearted person to talk with, it was best example of russian hospitality. She guided us about our plans and locations.

Definitely recommended. Also, Alexander (her son) was very much involved with us. Persons like these really setting up good trends and making travelling easy.

thankful to them always.

Anna is a wonderful person. She wants to travel the world and let's the world come to her with open arms. Really happy to meet a special person like you. Not to forget Sasha, it was fun to hang out with him. He is a very intelligent boy. He has really cool currency collection and loves history.

text: Nikita is funny, positive and talkative guy, good cook and just a nice host, would like to meet him again!

Nikita was really awesome and lovely host, I really hope to meet him again. We went hiking, got great food and nice conversations. He's very helpful, hospital guy with a big heart and a friendly smile. Thank you for everything, it was a real pleasure to meet you Nikita! :)
Thanks for showing me Nha trang by bike, it was scaring but it was unique experience for me.....

Nikita really is the best kind of Couchsurfing host! He is so thoughtful, honestly wants to get to know his surfers, and he is also very trusting with his home. We were able to come and go as we pleased, and Nikita offered us great Nha Trang advice, as well as a map and directions around the city. He is very easy-going and tries to make time for his surfers even when he is very busy. He joined us for amazing Indian food near his home, and we all went to the cinema since it was so rainy!

To sum up, Nikita is the type of person you immediately feel comfortable around - laid-back, kind, and interesting. He even let us use his bed, as there were two of us surfing, and he fixed us breakfast both mornings since he had free time. He is truly a great guy, and we highly recommend him!

Nikita was a real pro and a pal and I wish we'd had more time together. He hosted us when it would have been way easier not to, and it was inspiring how casual and trusting he was with it. Whether you stay in Vietnam or find yourself in a new far flung place lets meet up again someday! :)

We hosted Niki before in our place in Phuket and this time he hosted us in his place at Nha Trang. His place is located in the most touristy (I think) place in Nha Trang, which makes it a very convenient place to stay. Beach, shops and restaurants are just walking distance. We were supposed to stay with him only for one night but because of Tet holidays, our plans have changed a little bit and we have stayed for a week. We were also supposed to sleep on the floor but because of our baby, Niki and the other couchsurfers let us sleep on the bed (we are very grateful for that). He hosts a lot of people and he have guests almost every night -- we met a lot of nice people from his place! In return of his kindness, we invited him to travel with us in Dalat. He's a nice host and would always love to hang out with you and get to know you. Thank you again for hosting us and you are always welcome in our place in Phuket and soon in Dalat too! ;)

I stayed two nights with Nikita in Nha Trang and Da lat! It was really interesting staying with him and his friends! Hope that we could meet again or if you come to my place, I will definetely host you! Best wishes and good luck.

Nikita was really kind to accept my almost last minute request  and so I stayed at his place together with three (or 2 and a half) other couchsurfers :) Nikita has a nice sunny apartment, funny neighbours and a cool rooftop to grill shrimps :D
I really enjoyed my stay, Nikita and his friends are really interesting and fun people to meet. They even arranged a birthday celebration for me! Thank you guys!!! And thank you Nikita for hosting, for coffee and for my birthday :)

Nikita is very good, ineresting and easy-going guy! My friend and I stayed at his place a couple of nights. We had a cool bbq evening on the roof top. Staying at his place was good and memorable experience.  Thank you one more time!:)  

Take care, 
R.

Nikita is very good men! We stayed in his place 2 night,  and it was interesting experience. We told about different things,  and made bbq on the roof. He is fanny and smart. Also he has very nice music.So, I hope to see him again!  Thank you, Nikita!

Nikita is a great host and a friendly person, it was interesting to talk to him. We only stayed one night, but had home cooked dinner together, and some beers :) Highly recommend to host or surf with him.

Staying with Nick was just amazing! Seriously. Nikita has turned to be one of my best hosts ever. Personally, he's really a good person, kind of unique nowadays. He was everything about politeness, joyful, positiveness, kindness with serenity of mind. Indubitably he helped us a loooot. It was not just help though, he actually just shared all of his time with us making us being a family. We did a lot together, we hanged out (it was crazy)), we ate in a real Vietnamese , not that touristic places, we went to a local party, we played guitar, we made a home party, we smoked shisha and dances salsa, we also saw cultural part of the city, churches and monuments, we finally were sitting on the roof which nobody know about talking about everything. I would never forget it, thanks God you are, Nick! Thank you from the bottom of my heart. see you in Shanghai!:)

If tea is actually good for your health, I won't die during the next 100 years, considering the amount Natalia offered me. They also have some of the best coffee I've had in ages!
Alex speaks English very well, turned out to me a great Altai valley advisor and shared some of his Russian political knowledge with me. If you decide to have alcohol together, which you probably will, be careful. He loves to spill stuff haha
The little girl Natasha is one of the loveliest ones I've ever met. If you don't fall in love with her, you should probably never ever have your own children.

All the best!
Daniel

We met in Italy during her trip to Europe and I hosted her for about three days. I was planing to go in India so it was really great to know that she lives in Mumbai and could host me and my boyfriend.
She and her boyfriend Max hosted us in a very nice home. They showed us some parts of Mumbai, we had some meals together and watched an Indian movie! 
Anya cooked for us breakfast and she also made an apple pie!!! 
We had a good time together and I really appreciated that she bought for us a typical local fruit, I wanted so badly to try it!  She also gave me a saree and I could never thank her for that, for everything!! 

It really felt like home. 

Hope to see you really soon! 
A huge hug from Italy, 

Larisa.

To be honest I visited her home for the first time during winter this year and it's was an memorable experience. We know each other from Bombay and she's been one of the best thing that happened to me. For me she is family now. If I have to write about her personally this post will never end.

I m happy that she is finally on couchsurfing and I been there to help and see her host her first guest. Hope she finds and meet amazing people here on this platform and have amazing experience.

About her place. She calls it a cottage in her way but it's is a mansion build with love and hardwork by her and her mother. It's is a work in progress and everytime I visit it it gets better. 

I can proudly say during my first visit I was there helping her build our memorial "Out very own Taj Mahal" and on my 2nd visit to see it functional. 

For all the people who would either host or be her guest, better be good to her else I will be knocking at your door someday.

Vitaliy picked me up at the airport early morning when I arrived to Novosibirsk after a snowstorm.  Although the roads were snowy, he was an excellent driver because he used to race cars on ice before.  He drove me into town and showed me some sights, including the St. Nicholas chapel, which is the middle of Russia.  He was knowledgeable about his city and showed me statues, original old houses, famous churches, the theater, and the city center.  We had breakfast at People's Cafe.  Although I didn't stay overnight at his place, I was really happy to meet him because he is friendly, helpful, and introduced me to the city when I arrived.  Thanks for your time and nice meeting you.  Hope to see you another time!

Vitaliy and his family invited us to their beautiful house, which is only 30 minutes south from the city center of Nowosibirsk.
They have a huge garden with a large variety of fruits, vegetables and herbes.
 
We had a great weekend full of: Russian and English lessons, a sailing regatta of the kids, playing the drums and a famous German board game. We were also cooking together.
From the start we had the feeling we are part of the family and that they wanted to spend time with us. All plans for the Weekend were made together. We got to know a lot about Russian culture and quisine. If you're travelling to Nowosibirsk, you have to visit Vitaliy and his lovely family.  

Vitaliy, you rock! Thank you for this lovely weekend and unique experience.

Steffi and Chris from Berlin.
Denis was a really nice guy to have around, a great cook and an interesting traveler. Easy going and easy to live with.

Denis was a great guest at our home. He was super friendly, speaks both English and Russian, and fit right in with everyone else. If you host him, maybe he will dance, play beer pong, or cook with you. He embodies the Couchsurfing spirit. Best of luck in your travels Denis!

Olga stayed a couple of nights at my home in January 2018.   She was friendly and chatty and it was really interesting to learn about life in her home country and her motorcycle travels. Olga was a wonderful guest. She stayed with us 2 nights and we really enjoyed talking to her about our different cultures and travel. She communicated well with us, was punctual and cleaned up. Olga is one of the most interesting travelers I've met. She rides her motorcycle all around the world and stayed at my house on her trek across the US. She had great stories and spoke English well. She left my place tidier than when she arrived and even did the dishes that I had left in the sink. I felt comfortable with her and would definitely host her again.

Olga is so interesting! So brave! And so Kind!

Olga is a beautiful person !!! Together we toured the city and shared a wonderful day. She was really very generous with me! I hope we see each other again !! It will always be welcome at my home in Australia or Argentina :)

It was the biggest luck for me to meet Olga in my travel of Russia.  I stayed at her house 3nights. She was my host and friend, city guide and also the best helper in Novosibirsk. 
Furthermore, she is an amazing motorcycle traveller, so whenever we talked about our travel, it was always interesting and fun. 
She took me a Rock concert to see her friend's playing and was so nice. Also she cooked for us and tried to help me as much as she could.
I on my heart hope to meet her again someday, somewhere in the road.
If Couchsurfing is not only looking for a place to stay but for making a good friend, maybe she is the most suitable person on Couchsurfing.

text:
Lidia kindly offered to host me when I went to Novosibirsk to pass the GRE General Test. I had an opportunity to rest, sleep enough and complete the required preparations before the exam; she is very kind and helpful:) Lydia planned to go for a walk with me the half of a day after the exam, but later she realized she got busy for that time. Nevertheless, we talked more than an hour in the morning and more than an hour in the evening; she is a good listener, open-minded, asks reasonable questions and is rather smart. Also she is much busy, good fit, and promotes healthy lifestyle:)
From her story, I've concluded that she is especially interested in foreigners from far away, and most helpful for them, which is very logical. Also she is looking for English practice and new scientific information in relevant fields. All in all, Lidya is a very nice host I would recommend.

–õ–∏–¥–∏—è met me at the train platform and was waiting for me as soon as I stepped off the train, very impressive. We walked around Novosibirsk, went to eat food and in the evening we walked across the city to a river. I would definitely recommend staying with –õ–∏–¥–∏—è. She made me breakfast in the morning. Her English is excellent, she's friendly, entertaining, hospitable and knows Novosibirsk well. I learned a lot about Russia from staying with her. I would stay with her again if I come back to Novosibirsk.

text:
Andrey was a really cool host. After picking me up from the train station he drove me to his place. It's kinda far away from the centre of Nowosibirsk,but you have everything you could need while traveling there. He also really helped me out ordering something I needed for my camera and Brought me to where I needed to go to pick it up. 
Also he was able to take a day off and just drove with me around town,s showing me interesting things and telling me a lot of information about life in Russia. So it was amazing how much time he was able to spend with me.

Thanks a lot, really appreciate everything and wish you best of luck for your dancing!

Andrey is super nice and hospitable person! He provided me everything a person could possibly need in the trip. Even though he had to work everyday, he always cooked for me :)

Thank you very much for everything! Hope to meet with you some day again :)

text:
Evgeny is that kind of person that gives all for nothing. From the first moment He helped us a lot to organize our trip to Altai mountains, giving us info, links, finding transports, and all that before We met. He also arranged a car to travel from Barnaul to Kurai with his nice friend couple, Polina & Pasha, great people.

Despite We were about to cancel the staying in Akademgorodok, He was really comprehensive. Finally We were able to arrive on date, because He managed a BlaBlaCar for us, and We discovered the awesome couple Nadya & Eugeny are. 

We fell in love with them. Funny people, with nice hobbies, first class world travellers, thoughtful and hospitable.

They hosted us two days in their cozy apartment. We spent time with them chatting, having dinners and lunch, drinking wine and taking a walk on Akademgorodok.

We're grateful with you, and hope to see you soon guys, some where around the world, in our home in Alicante, or in our wayback to Siberia to experience a mad winter.
Nadya and Evgeny are so kind and easy-going! We really enjoy our time with them! Thank you for every thing! Nos vemos en Argentina!

text: Evgeny and his wife Nadya are definitely great hosts! They always have nice things to talk about, besides being very helpful in anything you may need. I (Luciano) stayed one night with them and it was really excellent, starting from the delicious dinner cooked by Nadya, passing through the nice red wine served by Evgeny and finishing on a nice talk about places in the world (just like me, they are travelling addicts). If you're going to Novosibirsk, you should definitely stay with them. Thank you very much for the couch and hope to see both of you again soon, somewhere in the world!

To stay with Evgeny and Nadya was such a wonderful experience because of their inviting lifestyle, their funny humour, their interesting hobbies they were sharing with us and of course their beautiful accommodation! We had three very nice days spending together on ice, in banya, with pancakes, good coffee and wine! Thanks for your time!

Oh! Evgeny and his beautiful wife Nadya made the day in Novosibirsk! They showed us Akademy Town, told some stories about education and it was nice to talk about travelling with a cup of delicious tea at their cozy home!
fromPublicAddressDescription: Nizhnevartovsk, Khanty-Mansi Autonomous Okrug, Russian Federation

Oh.my god... Vladimir and Rita~ 
Who said Russian people is cold? You should met them! They are such warm , friendly, thoughtful, kind,generous, nice.. amazing couple! I love them!

text:
Svetlana is a very special person with a biiig heart. We were so impressed how good is she, helping all travelers and people in need. Felt really thankful to meet such an awesome person and be her guest for few days. The flat she lives in is always full with travelers and really interesting place to spend time.
Thank you, Sveta! Waiting to see you soon in Bulgaria!
What one will remember about her is how delightful she was and curious about where one has been or will go. It was fun to stay with her and her roommates!
Very good. My last hope.
I with my friends are in need of accommodation but in spite of the difficulties Svetlana came into our situation and has taken us to yourself

Seasoned old hand or enthusiastic newbie, you're almost GUARANTEED surprise at HOW apt at being both guest and host Sveta is! Small wonder, though, given her vast experience AND outstanding personality.
Thank you for the very positive experience

Sveta helped me on CS last minute request. It was so nice of her. She is very smart girl. She showed me some parts of the city and adviced me where to go.

If you want to learn more about hitchhiking, Sveta is the right person from who you can learn a lot. :)

Thank you very much for all your help.

Svetlana hosted me and two fiends for a short stop-over in Novosibirsk.

Thanks a lot for sharing your small place with us. Keep on hitch-hiking and discovering! All the best 
Marian, balu and Jule

Very very positive experience. Svetlana is MONSTER of hosting, she hosted several thousand hitch-hikers. Unbielivable! Nothing about comfort, but dozen of hitch-hikers everyday. Be careful, it is not a tipical CS couch :)
Svetla is a funny girl, very nice, with a great sense of humor, agreeable and kind. She welcomed us with open arms. We shared beautiful moments together, and it was a real pleasure to have met her!

My friend and I arrived in Novosibirsk at 3 am, and began to look for where to stay. Svetlana was the only one who responded to our request and sheltered us for the night. 

Svetlana is a very friendly and open person. Moderately open minded ;) 

The next day we had a performance at the concert and Svetlana came to us and supported us. after the concert she fed us a delicious meal, and we had a wonderful talk for several hours. 

Svetlana is exactly what you are looking for in this site. 

Thank you, Sveta! See you later :)

Svetlana is exactly what you likes on couchsurfing. She is calm, nice, takes care of you, smiles, laughs... She made me appreciate Novossibirsk despite the weather (-24¬∞!). We discussed a lot about everything and that was perfect! You are more than welcome in france when I come back! Thanks for all and precious Russian words (Hibou ? üòÅ)

Svetlana and her family welcomed us as brothers <3 
They offered us their bedroom, we have known their friends (AMAZING PEOPLE) and they brought us to party on Saturday night, and we had an unforgettable evening!!! :) 
They are so beautiful persons, so difficult to find. 
If you go to Novosibirsk do not miss a chance to meet Svetlana and his family! 
Thanks guys, we will never forget you and we wait for you in Milan to make you fat! ;D

I was so lucky to have Svetlana as my host in Novosibirsk. She's friendly, open-minded person, and her home is perfect for staying. It was great to speak with Sveta about everything). I strongly recommend her as a couchsurfer to anyone who's get a chance to meet her!

The perfect host, I left feeling totally refreshed. Thanks for taking me in at the last minute and making me feel immediately at home after a long day. Such a shame I couldn't stay for longer to explore the city and get to know you better. See you in London and thank you again! Enjoy Montenegro!
fromPublicAddressDescription: London, England, United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland

text: Sveta is very kindly and interesting person :)

Sveta, her sister and brother are really cool hosts. They are smart, educated and open-minded so interesting conversations and good time is provided. Girls always wanted to hang out, so even if they were working and we spent there only 3 days it was a great time. They have comfortable and good located flat, so for exploring center of Novosybirsk you can forget about public transport.
Thank you guys for your invitation and great time together !

Svetlana is a very smart and fun girl, and a very good host. She has a very nice conversation and many interests, with a very promising future as a spanish speaker! To stay at her place, with her sister and brother, was a very comfortable and enjoyable experience, that I recommend to everyone. The place is good located!

Svetlana was a great host who lives in the very center of the city. We had a fun time walking around the city the first day and going to the event i planned on the second night. We stayed out until the morning! I loved hearing about her work as a waste water engineer because it is something I have never heard about before. Good luck with your plans!! :)

I stayed Svetlana for three times in my journey. I had some another invitations from hosts but this cheerful and hospitable family (Svetlana lives with her brother and sister) melted my heart and i accepted their offer to return with great pleasure!:-)
We spent a lot of time together with their friends and it was really cool time!)

Come to Saint-P!
Will be glad to see you again!
